[["/html[1]/body[1]/div[3]/article[1]/div[1]/div[3]/div[1]/div[2]/section[1]/div[1]/div[1]/div[1]/div[1]/h3[1]/text()[1]","Story highlights"],["/html[1]/body[1]/div[3]/article[1]/div[1]/div[3]/div[1]/div[2]/section[1]/div[1]/div[1]/div[1]/div[1]/ul[1]/li[1]/text()[1]","Airstrike hits judge's home, killing him and six family members"],["/html[1]/body[1]/div[3]/article[1]/div[1]/div[3]/div[1]/div[2]/section[1]/div[1]/div[1]/div[1]/div[1]/ul[1]/li[2]/text()[1]","Saudi coalition spokesman denies the home was deliberately targeted, says \"we do not attack residential sites\""],["/html[1]/body[1]/div[3]/article[1]/div[1]/div[3]/div[1]/div[2]/section[1]/div[1]/div[2]/p[1]/cite[1]/text()[1]","Sanaa, Yemen (CNN)"],["/html[1]/body[1]/div[3]/article[1]/div[1]/div[3]/div[1]/div[2]/section[1]/div[1]/div[2]/p[1]/text()[1]","A judge who once prosecuted now-exiled Yemeni President Abdu Rabu Mansour Hadi for treason was killed in a Saudi-led coalition airstrike Monday morning, two Yemeni Defense Ministry officials and a Houthi Defense Ministry official told CNN."],["/html[1]/body[1]/div[3]/article[1]/div[1]/div[3]/div[1]/div[2]/section[1]/div[1]/p[1]/text()[1]","Yemeni Judge Yahya Rubaid  was killed in his home, along with his wife, son, daughter-in-law and three grandchildren. Five other family members and two guards who were at the home were also injured. "],["/html[1]/body[1]/div[3]/article[1]/div[1]/div[3]/div[1]/div[2]/section[1]/div[1]/p[2]/text()[1]","Saudi coalition spokesman Brig. Gen. Ahmed Asseri denied claims that the airstrike targeted the home and civilians. "],["/html[1]/body[1]/div[3]/article[1]/div[1]/div[3]/div[1]/div[2]/section[1]/div[1]/p[3]/text()[1]","\"We do not target homes. We are looking for Scud missiles. We always confirm, we do not attack residential sites. We attack storage,\" Asseri told CNN by telephone. "],["/html[1]/body[1]/div[3]/article[1]/div[1]/div[3]/div[1]/div[2]/section[1]/div[1]/p[4]/text()[1]","The judge and his family members are among thousands of Yemeni civilian casualties in this war."],["/html[1]/body[1]/div[3]/article[1]/div[1]/div[3]/div[1]/div[2]/section[1]/div[1]/div[5]/p[1]/text()[1]","According to the United Nations, there have been more than 8,100 civilian casualties -- wounded and killed -- since the start of the war in early 2015. Of those, more than 2,800 have been killed. The Houthi-controlled Health Ministry cites a much higher death toll of 7,000 since the war began nearly a year ago. "],["/html[1]/body[1]/div[3]/article[1]/div[1]/div[3]/div[1]/div[2]/section[1]/div[1]/div[5]/p[2]/text()[1]","The Houthis are a minority group, allied with Iran, that overthrew Hadi's government and seized power last year. Hadi is now exiled in Saudi Arabia."],["/html[1]/body[1]/div[3]/article[1]/div[1]/div[3]/div[1]/div[2]/section[1]/div[1]/div[5]/p[3]/text()[1]","The Saudi-led coalition, which includes the United Arab Emirates, Kuwait, Bahrain, Qatar and other countries, has launched airstrikes on Houthi positions in Yemen since March 2015, with a brief truce last summer. "],["/html[1]/body[1]/div[3]/article[1]/div[1]/div[3]/div[1]/div[2]/section[1]/div[1]/div[5]/p[4]/text()[1]","The latest Saudi airstrikes in Sanaa have raised the death toll in Yemen to at least 220 civilians in the past five days, Yemeni military spokesman Sharaf Luqman told CNN."],["/html[1]/body[1]/div[3]/article[1]/div[1]/div[3]/div[1]/div[2]/section[1]/div[1]/div[5]/p[5]/text()[1]","\"The Saudi attacks are not focused on military targets. At least 190 homes were attacked by airstrikes this week and eight factories. All of these targets were civilian private-owned businesses,\" said Ahmed Al-Bahri, a Houthi official in Sanaa."],["/html[1]/body[1]/div[3]/article[1]/div[1]/div[3]/div[1]/div[2]/section[1]/div[1]/div[5]/p[6]/text()[1]","Al-Bahri said coalition forces are attacking Yemeni factories and businesses to destroy the country's economic infrastructure. Last week, a major oil refinery was destroyed by Saudi airstrikes in Yemen's province of Hodieda, killing 15 civilians in the process. "],["/html[1]/body[1]/div[3]/article[1]/div[1]/div[3]/div[1]/div[2]/section[1]/div[1]/div[5]/p[7]/text()[1]","Battles on the ground escalated this week between Saudi-allied resistance fighters and Houthi-led forces, spreading to six Yemeni provinces, as Hadi's supporters tried to liberate cities controlled by the Houthis."],["/html[1]/body[1]/div[3]/article[1]/div[1]/div[3]/div[1]/div[2]/section[1]/div[1]/div[5]/p[8]/text()[1]","Meanwhile, in Hadi's new temporary capital, Aden, militants shot and killed a Yemeni colonel, Aden government official Col. Jamal Al-Shaabi said Sunday. "],["/html[1]/body[1]/div[3]/article[1]/div[1]/div[3]/div[1]/div[2]/section[1]/div[1]/div[5]/p[9]/text()[1]","The incident was the latest in a series of targeted killings since the Yemeni government forces -- with support from the Saudi-led coalition -- liberated Aden from the Houthis last July. "],["/html[1]/body[1]/div[3]/article[1]/div[1]/div[3]/div[1]/div[2]/section[1]/div[1]/div[5]/p[10]/text()[1]","At least 28 Aden government officials have been killed by militants over the last two months, including its former governor, who was assassinated in early December. "]]